headline: Fed comments, FedEx earnings, consumer data: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton takes a look at the top stories investors should watch on Tuesday, June 24. Federal Reserve Chairman Jerome Powell will testify before the House Financial Services Committee in the morning. Cleveland Fed president Beth Hammack will also be providing commentary. FedEx (FDX), BlackBerry (BB), and Carnival (CCL) will be releasing earnings results. The Consumer Confidence Index for the month of June will be published in the morning. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime here.

headline: Inside Fred Smith's FedEx empire & global commerce legacy
